{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d5e175bf-e2e8-4275-b823-cd7adb45a0fe","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest adapter by default.** Starting in 4.0, the SDK uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the sole runner and no longer ships the VSTest bridge. Since `vstest.console` relies on that bridge to discover tests, it finds nothing.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n**Option 1 – Re-enable the VSTest bridge** (minimal CI change):\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Option 2 – Migrate your CI to use `dotnet test`** (recommended long-term), which now speaks MTP natively. Replace `vstest.console MyAssembly.dll` with:\n\n```\ndotnet test MyProject.csproj\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply one of these fixes to your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2fb90716-50e5-43af-88fc-c3b862925fea","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a known breaking change in MSTest.Sdk. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.x, MSTest introduced the \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" (MTP) as a new test runner, but it was opt-in alongside the traditional VSTest integration. \n\nIn MSTest.Sdk 4.0+, the default changed: **VSTest compatibility is no longer enabled by default**. This means `vstest.console.exe` (and `dotnet test` using the VSTest runner) can no longer discover or run tests unless you explicitly opt back in.\n\nThe key property is `<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>` (or `<UseVSTest>`). In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, the VSTest bridge adapter is no longer included by default, so vstest.console can't find the tests.\n \nTo fix this, I can either re-enable VSTest compatibility by setting the bridge property to true in the project file, or migrate to using `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, which is now the default runner. The core issue is that MTP is the new standard in 4.x, and the VSTest adapter that allowed the old runner to work is gone unless explicitly restored.","outputTokens":771,"requestId":"7C1C:1986A2:1802B27:1B6B609:69F9602E"},"id":"55edf21c-c0f0-4d3c-bc71-6cf345f1d42e","timestamp":"2026-05-05T03:13:04.343Z","parentId":"746b0cd2-78f7-44da-88a2-03379b61a276"}
